<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-10-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-10-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="778" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d778">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2427.</note>
                        <head>[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico
                                        City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-10-18"><hi rend="italic">October 18,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The practically unanimous election of Madero is insured by the now
                            definitely ascertained result of the general elections of Sunday; also
                            the election of Pino Suarez by a substantial majority. This insures
                            complete carrying out of the revolutionary program.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>